# Tools

* Install [Anaconda](http://jupyter.readthedocs.io/en/latest/install.html) which is the best Python distribution for Data Science. Choose the Python 3.x bundle to help the community overcome the battle between Python 2.x and Python 3.x.

Prefer Linux over Windows and make yourself familiar with the command line. 

Skills

Make yourself familiar with the Linux command line. This includes basic commands [such as these](http://www.gregreda.com/2013/07/15/unix-commands-for-data-science/) and more elaborated tools like [these ones](http://jeroenjanssens.com/2013/09/19/seven-command-line-tools-for-data-science.html).
